<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Pirate Multicarts??]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6847&amp;p=66222#p66222"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Xious wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Somebody feel free to correct me, but I think that a Mapper-0 ROM will, or can easily be made to run on an MMC3 board, this making the series on one cart possible.<br /></div><br />Running an NROM game on an MMC3 board takes two things. First, the menu just has to write all mapper registers to set up CHR banks 0, 2, 4, 5, 6, and 7, and PRG banks 0 and 1. Then, because MMC3 doesn't support switching $E000, multiple games on one MMC3 cartridge still need a second mapper to switch which super-bank (in the SUROM sense) is visible.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Aug 18, 2010 4:37 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
